commit.message: include license in manifest
Bump to 1.0.3, change setup.py to pull version info from source code
Removed setup.cfg since it wasn't used. Added Denilson to the AUTHORS list, and bumped the version number.

Merge pull request #1 from denilsonsa/hackingaround

Adding more tests, adding iPython notebook, reducing the amount of duplicate code

Each horizontal tick now means 0.1 increment.

I had to use `linspace(0, 1, 11)` instead of `linspace(0, 1, 10)`.

Removing duplicate README files with different extensions.

A single one is enough. :)
Adding an iPython notebook (AKA Jupyteri notebook) with the available functions.

Bumping version from 1.0.1 to 1.0.2.

Also making sure the `/` division is always floating point.

PEP-8 on basicTests.py

Also changed the quoting at the docstring to match `__init__.py`.

_checkRange(n) function, and making Elastic functions call each other.

To avoid duplicate code, I've moved the `if not 0 <= n <= 1` check to a
separate function, and called it everywhere. It avoids repeating the
same error string everywhere, and it is a bit more readable. It may be a
tiny bit slower, due to the additional function call, but it is
negligible.

The Elastic easing functions were the most complex ones in this module.
Default argument values were used to remove a bunch of conditionals.
Also, two of those functions were rewritten to call the first one, just
like the Bounce functions already do.

Small PEP-8 fixes.

There are 47 occurences of *E501 line too long*, and I'm not going to
fix those.
Adding tests for tweening functions.
Adding doctest to tests.
Changed tests to put the local pytweening module at the start of the module paths. Removed tests for getExtendedLine() since that function was deprecated.
Renamed getLinePoint() to getPointOnLine(). Bumped version to 1.0.1
Added comments to the tweening functions.
Corrected casing in PyTweening name
Adding graphs showing the tween functions.
Prepping for pypi upload.
Initial commit
